WEBVTT

00:00.934 --> 00:03.504
My name is Earl.

00:03.571 --> 00:06.006
[ Earl Narrating ] Randy has
several issues when he sleeps.
[ Snoring ]

00:06.074 --> 00:09.243
He grinds his teeth,
he occasionally
punches me in the face,

00:09.310 --> 00:12.413
and he doesn't always breathe.
[ Stops Breathing ]

00:12.480 --> 00:16.217
And although temporarily
dying 12 times a night
didn't bother Randy,

00:16.284 --> 00:18.352
it sure bothered me.

00:34.302 --> 00:38.372
[ Snorts,
Resumes Breathing ]
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

00:41.075 --> 00:43.611
** [ TV: Program Theme ]

00:43.677 --> 00:46.880
I'm Nicole Moses with the
Up Before Dawn News Report.

00:46.947 --> 00:50.318
Looking first to traffic--

00:50.384 --> 00:54.355
There is no traffic
because nobody's up yet.

00:54.422 --> 00:57.191
[ Earl Narrating ]
But bein' awake at 4:00 a.m.
must have been karma's way...

00:57.258 --> 00:59.593
of telling me to do
number 29 on my list--

00:59.660 --> 01:01.762
harassed a reporter.

01:01.829 --> 01:03.964
It all started
back when I was married to Joy.

01:04.031 --> 01:06.700
[ Loud Explosion ]

01:06.767 --> 01:08.569
Was that the Alcotts'
meth lab?
[ Car Alarms Blaring ]

01:08.636 --> 01:11.472
The Alcotts are close.
Would've been hit by debris.

01:11.539 --> 01:15.576
- [ Debris Raining On Roof ]
- It was the Alcotts.

01:15.643 --> 01:17.545
People who are on meth
shouldn't make meth.

01:17.611 --> 01:19.580
It's always
the second batch that blows.

01:19.647 --> 01:22.516
[ Earl Narrating ]
Exploding trailers were
pretty common where we lived,

01:22.583 --> 01:25.085
but this one was special
'cause a celebrity
blew up in it.

01:25.153 --> 01:27.488
[ Nicole ]
Buck West, owner
of the I Come to You...

01:27.555 --> 01:29.890
and Clean Your Dog
with My Own Supplies...

01:29.957 --> 01:32.660
Mobile Pet Grooming Company,
is dead.

01:32.726 --> 01:34.662
Apparently, his love
for clean animals...

01:34.728 --> 01:37.531
was outweighed by his love
for crystal meth.

01:37.598 --> 01:41.935
Hey, dummy!
You and your stupid brother
are on TV!

01:42.002 --> 01:46.340
The family asked that donations
in the name of Mr. West
be made to the family.

01:46.407 --> 01:48.876
[ Nicole On TV ]
Buck West lived his life
to the fullest.

01:48.942 --> 01:52.079
Crazy arms!
I got crazy arms.
I can't control 'em.

01:52.146 --> 01:54.915
Oh, snap.
I gotta record this.
[ TV Continues, Indistinct ]

01:54.982 --> 01:57.451
[ Earl Narrating ]
Luckily, Joy just finished
tapin' Wheel of Fortune,

01:57.518 --> 01:59.687
so the camcorder was handy.

01:59.753 --> 02:01.555
[ Mutters ]
Stop it!

02:01.622 --> 02:03.691
Also reported killed
in the explosion...

02:03.757 --> 02:05.759
were two drifters,
a homeless man and a bum.
Whoo!

02:05.826 --> 02:09.129
[ Groans ]
No berry twisters!
No berry twisters!

02:09.197 --> 02:11.131
[ Groaning ]

02:11.199 --> 02:14.101
[ Earl Narrating ]
And as fun as it was
acting stupid on live TV,

02:14.168 --> 02:15.936
it was even more fun
the next day...

02:16.003 --> 02:18.105
when we found out other people
had enjoyed it too.

02:18.172 --> 02:21.074
[ Crowd Cheering ]
Hey, Earl.

02:21.141 --> 02:23.177
You guys were funny.

02:23.244 --> 02:25.879
A lot of folks were upset
about that meth lab
blowin' up,

02:25.946 --> 02:28.749
but you and your "crazy arms"
helped 'em smile again.

02:28.816 --> 02:30.818
Yeah. That was
the best thing
on television...

02:30.884 --> 02:34.222
since that overly aggressive
minister climbed into
that gorilla's cage...

02:34.288 --> 02:37.725
to try to baptize it.

02:37.791 --> 02:39.827
[ Earl Narrating ]
Crazy arms was sweepin'
the Crab Shack,

02:39.893 --> 02:41.862
and me and Randy were
the proudest brothers...

02:41.929 --> 02:44.332
since Eddie Van Halen
and his drummer brother.

02:45.733 --> 02:48.135
And just like Van Halen,
we were gonna keep playin'...

02:48.202 --> 02:50.338
until everybody got sick of us.

02:50.404 --> 02:52.406
We're here at the
ribbon-cutting ceremony...

02:52.473 --> 02:55.676
of Camden's newest
drug-and-alcohol
treatment center...

02:55.743 --> 02:58.412
with local celebrity
TV's Tim Stack.

02:58.479 --> 03:00.414
Local?

03:00.481 --> 03:03.784
Would Pat Sajak have dinner
with a local celebrity?

03:03.851 --> 03:07.621
- This drug-and-alcohol
treatment-- center.
- Yeah! Yeah!

03:07.688 --> 03:11.392
I'm Nicole Moses, live.
Back to you.
[ Chattering, Barking ]

03:11.459 --> 03:13.961
[ Earl Narrating ]
Me and Randy had given
Channel 3 its biggest ratings...

03:14.027 --> 03:16.664
since the chick who spun
the lottery wheel's
boob fell out.

03:16.730 --> 03:19.132
Live report.
Here comes los brazos locos.

03:19.199 --> 03:23.471
Zoo officials stress
the escaped bear is agitated
and extremely dangerous,

03:23.537 --> 03:26.340
despite how agreeable
bears are often depicted
in cartoons.

03:26.407 --> 03:28.342
[ Growling ]
Authorities--

03:28.409 --> 03:30.778
- [ All Laughing ]
- Give me some honey!

03:30.844 --> 03:36.284
I got him!
Authorities say the bear most
likely escaped overnight...

03:36.350 --> 03:38.486
during a training session--

03:40.854 --> 03:43.657
Silly brazos locos.

03:43.724 --> 03:47.528
[ Earl Narrating ] When we
ran out of news events to crash,
we started makin' up our own.

03:47.595 --> 03:49.597
We're here at Pimmit Hills
Trailer Park...

03:49.663 --> 03:52.232
where a baby has just
been reported missing.

03:52.300 --> 03:54.668
My baby--
My baby is missing.

03:54.735 --> 03:57.971
I don't know what to do.
He is just a baby.

03:58.038 --> 04:00.040
[ Muffled Crying ]

04:00.107 --> 04:02.175
Oh, my God!
That's him.

04:02.242 --> 04:05.613
That's my missin' baby
in the fridge.
Follow me on this. Follow me.

04:05.679 --> 04:09.016
I'm trying to get to the fridge
to save this sweet baby's life!

04:10.551 --> 04:13.621
- Goo-goo! Ga-ga!
- [ Crowd Laughing ]

04:13.687 --> 04:17.190
"Cwazy" arms.
Cwazy arms.

04:17.257 --> 04:20.361
This is not funny.
You people are not funny!

04:20.428 --> 04:22.363
I am a serious journalist!

04:22.430 --> 04:25.766
And you are just trailer trash!
Trailer trash!
[ Microphone Thumping ]

04:25.833 --> 04:28.001
Mayonnaise-lovin'
cousin humpers!

04:28.068 --> 04:30.904
[ Earl Narrating ]
That was the day we finally
pushed Nicole too far.

04:30.971 --> 04:34.107
[ Screaming ]
After that, Nicole's career
went down the tubes.

04:34.174 --> 04:36.677
Randy, wake up.
[ Gasps ]

04:36.744 --> 04:38.746
We gotta go
to the news station.

04:38.812 --> 04:42.450
I just saw Nicole Moses.
Oh, thank God
you woke me.

04:42.516 --> 04:44.852
I just had
an eight-hour dream
about a ball of yarn.

04:44.918 --> 04:46.787
It was so borin'.

04:46.854 --> 04:50.157
I kept tryin'
to go to sleep,
but I already was.

04:50.223 --> 04:53.861
[ Earl Narrating ] Later
that morning, me and Randy
went down to the TV station.

04:53.927 --> 04:56.029
While I explained
my karma list to Nicole,

04:56.096 --> 04:59.299
Randy looked around for answers
about how TV was made.

04:59.367 --> 05:03.070
He always hoped there was
a machine that shrunk down
people and furniture to TV size.

05:03.136 --> 05:05.773
He didn't see anything
that looked like a ray gun,

05:05.839 --> 05:08.075
but he did find something else
that made him curious.

05:10.177 --> 05:12.880
I want to put you
on the news.
Me, on the news?

05:12.946 --> 05:14.915
Yes. I just need one great
heartwarming story,

05:14.982 --> 05:16.950
and my boss
will give me another shot.

05:17.017 --> 05:19.086
Nick Chavez did a story
about Siamese twins...

05:19.152 --> 05:22.289
getting a little cart
so the big one could take
the little one to the mall...

05:22.356 --> 05:24.291
and they put him
in the anchor spot.

05:24.358 --> 05:27.127
I remember that story--
Kiki and Tiki.

05:27.194 --> 05:30.230
They went to Foot Locker,
but the salesman wouldn't
let them buy three shoes.

05:30.297 --> 05:34.968
It's perfect.
I can see the tagline already--
"From hood to good."

05:35.035 --> 05:38.338
We start with one
of your mug shots,
then fade to a list item.

05:38.406 --> 05:41.141
Can you give a bath
to a crippled lady?

05:41.208 --> 05:44.912
I could. It's not on my list,
but they don't scare me
or nothin'.

05:44.978 --> 05:46.980
No, that's okay.
We'll get something good
from the list.

05:56.857 --> 05:59.026
Would I have to memorize
lines or anything?

05:59.092 --> 06:02.763
Words go right through my head,
unless it's a Polish joke
or a Judas Priest song.

06:02.830 --> 06:05.198
No. No memorization
and no jokes.

06:05.265 --> 06:07.234
Just you talking about you.

06:07.300 --> 06:09.770
Well, if you think
it'll help,

06:09.837 --> 06:12.105
I guess
I'm gonna be on TV.

06:20.247 --> 06:24.418
[ Screams ]

06:24.485 --> 06:28.456
[ Screaming Continues ]

06:32.159 --> 06:34.695
[ Earl Narrating ]
I was lookin' forward
to bein' on the TV news...

06:34.762 --> 06:37.965
as an actual invited guest,
and so was Randy.

06:38.031 --> 06:40.133
I can't decide
whether to comb my hair.

06:40.200 --> 06:43.203
I want to look presentable,
but I want people
to recognize me.

06:43.270 --> 06:45.506
[ Sniffing ]

06:46.874 --> 06:49.610
You smell good.
Aftershave.

06:49.677 --> 06:52.079
But don't try puttin' any
on your downstairs.
It burns.

06:52.145 --> 06:57.217
Man, bein' a TV star
is complicated.
[ Sniffs ]

06:57.284 --> 06:59.987
[ Earl Narrating ]
Back when we pestered Nicole,
it was easy bein' on TV...

07:00.053 --> 07:02.355
'cause I didn't care
what people thought.

07:02.422 --> 07:06.326
But now that I did care
what people thought,
bein' on TV made me nervous.

07:06.393 --> 07:10.430
Okay, Earl,
why don't you tell us
how the list began?

07:10.498 --> 07:12.600
All right. I, uh--

07:15.368 --> 07:17.671
[ Clears Throat, Blows ]
I, uh--

07:17.738 --> 07:22.075
- No, no. No, let it go.
Don't touch it.
- Sorry.

07:22.142 --> 07:25.412
- [ Shouting ] It all started
back when I was--
- Okay, cut!

07:25.479 --> 07:27.581
Can we do a wireless mike
on him?

07:27.648 --> 07:31.118
- Please. Thank you.
- If you wanna strap
one of them mikes on me,

07:31.184 --> 07:33.353
I got a buttonhole here
that's missin' a button.

07:33.420 --> 07:36.323
It got caught when I was
ridin' down an escalator
on my belly.

07:36.389 --> 07:38.692
It's a good story.
If you wanna turn
the cameras here--

07:38.759 --> 07:42.029
Jim, no. The light's
gonna be in the shot.

07:42.095 --> 07:44.565
[ Sighs ]
Come on, people.
Help me out here.

07:44.632 --> 07:46.567
I don't wanna spend
the rest of my career...

07:46.634 --> 07:48.669
doing the crop report
with a sock-puppet rooster.

07:48.736 --> 07:50.804
[ High-pitched Voice ]
Cock-a-doodle mornin',
Nicole.

07:50.871 --> 07:54.274
Why don't you tell us
about the situation
with the boll weevils?

07:54.341 --> 07:57.177
Okay, Earl,
why don't you just tell us
how you pick a list item?

07:57.244 --> 07:59.312
And... action.

07:59.379 --> 08:02.683
Well, sometimes I just
close my eyes and point to one.

08:02.750 --> 08:05.018
Like this.
Oh.

08:05.085 --> 08:07.955
Looks like you cost someone
a very important client.

08:08.021 --> 08:11.592
By the way,
"client" is with a "C."
He's a diamond in the rough.

08:11.659 --> 08:15.495
I'm sorry. I have
to do that again. Wait.

08:15.563 --> 08:19.199
He's a diamond...
in the rough.
Print it.

08:19.266 --> 08:22.469
You lost this woman
a valuable client,
and she works here?

08:22.536 --> 08:24.605
Well, today, she does.

08:27.507 --> 08:30.778
- Hey, Earl.
- Patty, I need to talk to you
about somethin' on my list.

08:30.844 --> 08:33.681
All right. One sec. I just gotta
give this perv a baby bottle,

08:33.747 --> 08:35.749
burp him, spank him,
powder him, change him,

08:35.816 --> 08:37.751
rock him to sleep,
and then I'm done here.

08:37.818 --> 08:40.153
Wait.
That's the businesswoman?

08:40.220 --> 08:41.955
Okay. Cut, cut.

08:42.022 --> 08:44.658
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my God.
Nicole Moses.

08:44.725 --> 08:47.094
People always tell me
that we look exactly the same.

08:47.160 --> 08:49.597
Do people ever tell you
you look like a daytime hooker?

08:49.663 --> 08:51.632
'Cause if they do,
that's me.

08:52.933 --> 08:55.569
We can't do a story
about you helping a hooker.

08:55.636 --> 08:58.405
This has to be heartwarming
and emotional.

08:58.471 --> 09:01.008
I need a Kiki and Tiki.
No, no. Wait.

09:01.074 --> 09:04.377
I can do heartwarmin'.
I got heartwarmin'
on here.

09:04.444 --> 09:08.048
I got a heartwarmin' story.
Remember that finger
we found in the park?

09:08.115 --> 09:11.318
We could try
to find who it belongs to.
Randy, just let me think.

09:12.820 --> 09:16.356
Here's one. Number 40--
wrecked the kids' playhouse.

09:16.423 --> 09:18.959
[ Earl Narrating ]
Dodge and Earl Jr.
loved that playhouse.

09:19.026 --> 09:21.695
Let's sleep in here
tonight.
I'm scared.

09:21.762 --> 09:23.931
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

09:23.997 --> 09:27.234
- [ Loud Squeaking, Clattering ]
- Aliens!

09:27.300 --> 09:29.770
[ Both Screaming ]

09:32.673 --> 09:35.042
See, Randy?

09:35.108 --> 09:37.210
You thought I couldn't
make it all the way home.

09:39.279 --> 09:41.314
Randy?

09:43.016 --> 09:44.952
Randy?

09:45.018 --> 09:46.954
Oh, crap.

09:47.020 --> 09:49.089
[ Dogs Barking In Distance ]

09:51.424 --> 09:54.762
Man makes up for ruining
children's dreams.
It's perfect.

09:54.828 --> 09:57.164
The public loves
stories of redemption.

09:57.230 --> 09:59.366
Crap. We only have time
to shoot the intro.

09:59.432 --> 10:03.103
Let's shoot over there.
I think the guy in the car
just paid for another round.

10:03.170 --> 10:06.940
Excuse me. Reporter lady,
am I gonna be on the camera
pretty soon?

10:07.007 --> 10:09.376
'Cause I don't know
how long my cowlick
is gonna stay down.

10:09.442 --> 10:11.344
What? Oh.

10:11.411 --> 10:14.014
Big fella, no, you're not
gonna be on the camera.

10:14.081 --> 10:16.684
The story's about Earl.
I hope I didn't mislead you.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.086
Huh? Oh, no, no, no.

10:19.152 --> 10:21.388
I didn't think I was
gonna be in the show.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.991
I didn't even wanna be.

10:24.057 --> 10:25.959
See?

10:26.860 --> 10:30.297
[ People Chattering ]

10:30.363 --> 10:32.132
Hey, dummy.
What's wrong?

10:32.199 --> 10:34.668
World run out
of macaroni and cheese?

10:34.735 --> 10:36.636
[ Laughs ]

10:36.704 --> 10:38.605
Seriously though.
What's your trouble?

10:38.672 --> 10:42.375
Stupid reporter lady
won't let me be in her story
about Earl's list.

10:42.442 --> 10:44.177
That's because
it's his list.

10:44.244 --> 10:46.579
Karma hit him
with a car, not you.

10:46.646 --> 10:50.183
I help him cross things off,
plus he couldn't have done
half the bad things on there...

10:50.250 --> 10:53.854
if I wasn't with him
smashin' windows and
givin' him a boost and stuff.

10:53.921 --> 10:56.757
There's your problem.
You're just givin' him
a boost.

10:56.824 --> 11:00.293
Who wants a story
about a man standin' there
pushin' up on another man's ass?

11:00.360 --> 11:03.563
If you wanna get noticed
in this world, you gotta
break away from your brother.

11:03.630 --> 11:05.498
You mean I gotta move
out of the motel?

11:05.565 --> 11:08.068
I don't know, Joy.
I don't like
payin' money for soap.

11:08.135 --> 11:11.104
I guess I could
make it myself.

11:11.171 --> 11:14.007
What are the ingredients?
There's soap. There's wrapper.
There's--

11:14.074 --> 11:15.976
You gotta stop doin'
whatever he does.

11:16.043 --> 11:18.078
When he was bad,
you were bad.

11:18.145 --> 11:20.147
When he turned good,
you turned good.

11:20.213 --> 11:22.482
You gotta be
your own man.
Do the opposite.

11:22.549 --> 11:24.918
When Earl zigs,
you gotta zag.

11:24.985 --> 11:27.888
The opposite of Earl.
I can do that.

11:27.955 --> 11:30.223
I'm gonna make a list
of all the good things
I've done...

11:30.290 --> 11:32.259
and go around
screwin' those people.

11:32.325 --> 11:34.494
And I'll wear a sombrero
while I'm doin' it.

11:34.561 --> 11:37.330
Earl never wears a sombrero.

11:37.397 --> 11:39.833
Scattered showers overnight
have authorities hoping
for relief...

11:39.900 --> 11:41.769
from the Nathanville
tire fire.

11:41.835 --> 11:43.771
What are you doin'?

11:43.837 --> 11:46.907
I'm practicing
my American accent by
watching your news-lady friend.

11:46.974 --> 11:50.643
[ Homogenized Accent ]
The weather today calls for
a high of 62 and a low of 48.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.479
Wow.

11:52.545 --> 11:56.683
If you talked like that
a couple months ago, you
wouldn't have gotten deported.

11:56.750 --> 11:58.551
And if that doesn't help,

11:58.618 --> 12:02.555
they're asking that people
stop adding tires to the fire.

12:02.622 --> 12:06.994
Crazy head! Crazy head's
comin' to town.
Get him off.

12:07.060 --> 12:09.629
Get off my set!
And behind him,
there's gonna be a twister.

12:09.696 --> 12:12.165
Get him off!
Crazy head!

12:12.232 --> 12:14.935
What the hell's he doin'?
What the hell happened
to his body?

12:15.002 --> 12:17.037
You guys! Help me.
Look at me.
I'm Pac-Man.

12:17.104 --> 12:20.373
Wok, wok, wok, wok, wok!
Wok, wok, wok, wok, wok!

12:20.440 --> 12:21.942
[ Steady Beeping ]

12:28.882 --> 12:32.986
- What's goin' on with you?
- I'm wearin' a sombrero,
which you would never do.

12:33.053 --> 12:35.088
I'm zagging
'cause you always zig.

12:35.155 --> 12:37.557
And I'm gonna be my own man
starting right--

12:37.624 --> 12:40.060
[ Farting ]
now.

12:40.127 --> 12:43.030
- Oh, Randy. God.
- That's me zaggin'.

12:43.096 --> 12:47.467
Usually I'd be nice like you
and go outside to rip one,
but I'm outta your shadow, Earl.

12:47.534 --> 12:50.470
I'm gonna get noticed
for being me and get
my own TV news report.

12:50.537 --> 12:53.706
Then it won't matter that
people don't give me credit
for being part of your list,

12:53.773 --> 12:55.843
'cause I'm doin'
my own thing.

12:55.909 --> 12:57.811
[ Crash ]
Zag.

12:57.878 --> 13:00.513
See? You would never do that,
would you, Earl?

13:00.580 --> 13:02.515
Oh, man! No, I wouldn't.

13:02.582 --> 13:05.385
And I'm pretty sure the news
is never gonna do a story...

13:05.452 --> 13:07.354
about a sombrero-wearin' jackass
who goes around breakin' lamps.

13:07.420 --> 13:09.356
You're wrong.
And when they do that story,

13:09.422 --> 13:11.424
I'm gonna make sure
my brother's a part of it,

13:11.491 --> 13:14.928
'cause that's something
you wouldn't do.

13:14.995 --> 13:17.898
So that's
what this is about?

13:19.066 --> 13:21.334
I'm sorry, Randy.

13:21.401 --> 13:24.437
I didn't even notice
that you were being
left out of the story.

13:24.504 --> 13:26.473
Nobody notices me.

13:26.539 --> 13:30.210
It's just like Joy said.
Karma hit you with that car,
not me.

13:30.277 --> 13:32.579
Randy, you're a big part
of the list.

13:32.645 --> 13:34.547
I know it,
you know it,

13:34.614 --> 13:36.850
and, when this story airs,
everyone's gonna know it.

13:36.917 --> 13:39.519
'Cause you're gonna be
right there with me
buildin' that playhouse.

13:39.586 --> 13:43.523
Really?
Absolutely.
Let's zig together, buddy.

13:43.590 --> 13:46.293
Tell the truth, Earl.
Was crazy head
funny on TV?

